download the package from fdf page
unzip the 'sources' file. It will become 'minilibx'
cd minilibx
sudo cp libmlx.a /usr/lib/X11/.
sudo cp libmlx_Linux.a /usr/lib/X11/.
sudo cp mlx.h /usr/include/.

Then make main.c file from online tutorial

compile like this: gcc main.c minilibx/libmlx_Linux.a -L/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu -lXext -lX11 -lm

